  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Let F be a field with positive odd characteristic p . We prove a variety of new sum-product type estimates over F . They are derived from the theorem that the number of incidences between m points and n planes in the projective three-space <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>P</mi><mi>G</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>F</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> , with <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>m</mi><mo>≥</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>O</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msup><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> , is <math altimg="si3.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>O</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>m</mi><msqrt><mi>n</mi></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>m</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>,</mo></math> where k denotes the maximum number of collinear planes.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
  </datafield>
